President Barack Obama announced his intention to nominate Jim Miller as Principal Deputy Under Secretary for Policy and Lt. Gen. Wallace "Chip" Gregson, Jr. (USMC, Ret) as Assistant Secretary for Asian and Pacific Security Affairs at the Department of Defense. The White House also stated that Mike Donley will remain as Secretary of the Air Force, Lt. Gen. James R. Clapper (USAF, Ret) will remain as Under Secretary of Defense for Intelligence, and Michael G. Vickers will remain as Assistant Secretary of Defense for Special Operations/Low Intensity Conflict and Interdependent Capabilities. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals' commitment and expertise to guide the Department of Defense and maintain a strong and effective military. The article provides background information on each nominee and their previous positions and accomplishments.